Acquire and Analyze macOS Disk Images with SleuthKit
Learning Objectives
By completing this lab, you will:

Install and configure SleuthKit on Linux for macOS forensic analysis
Create and acquire macOS disk images using dd and other forensic tools
Analyze macOS file systems (HFS+ and APFS) using SleuthKit commands
Extract key macOS artifacts including system logs, user data, and application files
Generate forensic reports from macOS disk image analysis
Prerequisites
Basic Linux command-line knowledge
Understanding of file systems and disk structures
Familiarity with forensic investigation concepts
Root/sudo access on Linux system
